caption: Convenient counter service to pick up. Always delicious. The brussel sprouts are to die for. The orange chicken and the lamb cumin are equally divine

I can never say enough about Chiko. I have been to both locations with at least 30+ orders over the years. They are consistently delicious- sometimes a little too spicy for my liking, but I just ask them to make it mild. Truly my favorite restaurant in DC.

Best lunch deal in town! The lunch bento boxes are large and delicious - you get an entree and two sides, enough for two meals. CHIKO’s Asian fusion is interesting and delicious, and a great place to stop by if you’re in the neighborhood.
I’m confused how this place doesn’t have 5 starts. Food was awesome!
Incredible food for a fair price!

Did carry out for dinner and the food ETA was ~20 mins. Tried calling to order, but didn't get a hold of anyone. They don't do substitutes, but you can add notes on your order online. Got there right on time and stood at the table they had blocking the door for COVID. Wasn't sure whether to push the button on the remote that was on the table or not, but a worker saw me and came out. Order was ready and came in a paper bag with two containers with lids, but no utensils or napkins (maybe they're trying to be eco-conscious). Food was still hot when I got back to where I was staying 20 mins later and was so good!  The prices seemed a little high for fast casual at first, but the portions are large enough to split between two meals (especially if you're not someone who tends to eat a lot in a single meal). I got the cumin lamb stir fry and it was spicier than I had anticipated and contained shiitake mushrooms, onions, fried shallots, green onions, cabbage or bokchoy, and fall-apart tender lamb. I ate mine out of the container, but the spices in the sauce all collected at the bottom, so if you're trying to distribute the spice evenly, I'd suggest putting it in a separate bowl and stirring. You can't even really taste that the noodles are wheat flour in case that's a concern. The other dish ordered was the Chicken+the Egg fried rice and it was also very tasty with a slight char to the rice (like in Korean stone pot rice). I think ordering a couple things and eating family style is the best way to go with their offerings.
Delicious takeout. Love the variety. Great place to get a twist on Asian cuisine!

I can't say enough amazing things. You have to get the food to go, but there were tables out front where we could sit and eat. The food was OUTSTANDING. we got dumplings, the bulgogi tots, hot fried chicken sandwich, crispy chicken bowl, and of course, the Kimchi back. Everything was so delicious and we cannot wait to go back!
Extraordinary vegetarian options at a reasonable price.

We got Chikko to-go last night and it was amazing! I have celiac, so there isn't a bunch of Chinese or Korean food that I can have, generally. But they have a bunch of GF options and they were delicious! I got the shrimp bowl and you'd have no idea the food was GF! Will definitely be coming back and highly recommend it!
Okay

I found this place on Instagram and I honestly wasn’t expecting to have literally the best food.  I got the chicken and coconut for desert. And honestly it hit the spot especially after the food was a bit spicy.  Everything was great hot and warm.
Get the cumin lamb noodles. Honestly though get anything, it's great.
Fabulous food and seamless order-online and pick-up process.

Food was amazing! such a nice surprise to order from a restaurant that totally surprises you on a good way, we had rice, noodles and the cauliflower.  Would definitely go back to this place to eat the next time i'm in town! During Lockdown they don't provide any utensils nor extra plates.  Had to ask a couple of time to get some, (we were staying at the hotel next door) which also didn't had any. At the end they agreed to give us some chopsticks and an extra empty container so we could eat. Thank you!

I got two dishes. I don’t think either were anything special. The half-a-cado salad which was the better of the two. I also got the stir fried rice cakes. It really lacked flavor and tasted like something I could make at home. I also get really annoyed when places have tofu but don’t offer it in there vegetarian dishes.
Get the snack sampler

I got the crispy chicken bowl. The textures and flavors of the first few bites were all spot on, though as I ate the saltiness became almost overbearing. Then before I finished the bowl I got incredibly nauseous. By some miracle I didn't vomit, but my stomach was upset the rest of the day.  I don't know if this was some sort of fluke, but I don't know if I'd be back if I lived in D.C.
Wow!! Not only is the food great, the service is the best I've ever experienced!!! Just wow. Every store should base customer service off this restaurant.

My girlfriend and I came here to celebrate 13 months together. We did the tasting menu at the kitchen counter and were very impressed with the whole experience. We started with the soju in-house cocktail that was perfectly balanced (I had two) and thirst-quenching. Then the side dishes came out, six in total, pretty amazing and full of diverse and rich flavors. The potato and egg salad, kimchi, chilled shrimp, and turmeric pickled daikon were my favorites. Next came the first wave of main menu items. Then another wave. Finally, dessert. The shrimp toast, chicken, smashed salmon, chopped brisket, and in-house spicy sauce were all equally amazing in their own right. I wish I had known the amount of food that would be served, for I would have skipped lunch. Lastly, all of the staff were very friendly and professional. Great conversation and music to compliment the whole experience. Will return, although not before trying the other locations first.

Everytime I go here I try so hard not to order the same thing... but then always end up getting the green beans. Everything on the menu packs a punch of flavor (and heat)! It's a great place to go for lunch if you work in the Dupont area or for dinner. Go in a group so you can get a bunch of dishes to share. It's small and no reservations (you place your order, pick up a number, and find a table) so you may have to wait but it moves quickly. They do have a chef's counter that you can book in advance - on my 2020 bucket list!
Slightly pricey.  Don't get the tots.
Absolutely delicious food in a casual atmosphere. The rib dish and the orange chicken are spectacular.
Very flavorful! The veggie l wok charred wheat noodles was amazing.

Very slow service... Food was ok, but the wait was too long, especially for take out. We waited so long that half the dining room opened up so thankfully they let us convert to dine in. But for some unknown reason our "chilled shrimp" still room an hour to serve up... This is something that you just grab out of the fridge and should have been the very first thing. Can't recommend coming back here

Second time here and I left a little disappointed. First time was fantastic! However, the second time I found both the vegetables and the kimchi stew bowl to be both way too clove heavy. To the point where I couldn't finish either due to the overwhelming flavor of the spice. Majority of their items that we have tried are spot on, but at the very least those couple items need to be rebalanced.

After a meal at Chiko you’ll be left wondering one key question, why?  Why is their “brisket” bowl $18 when it’s made out of 3 ingredients and rice? (Banana peppers, hard boiled egg and “brisket”) Why does their version of brisket taste like hot dog meat? And finally why does this place have good reviews?  All of their meals appear to be 3 ingredients, their avocado salad for example was made up of cucumbers, avocado, and radish.  Which is fine, but their price point is delusional, even for DC. Food was greasy and lackluster.  I went in starving and was sorely disappointed.  Finally, for a place that touts itself as fast casual, it seems odd that they default the suggested tip to 30% at the register.  I never mind tipping 20% or more, but 30% at a restaurant in which the only service you receive is them bringing a tray to your table I take issue.  If you want fusion, I highly recommend finding any other fusion restaurant in DC(Far East Taco Grill is Korean Mexican fusion and is amazing), as Chiko is an overpriced overhyped mess.

Wonderful service and flavorful, quick food! Small seating availability but cozy and comfortable if you happen to grab one. They have a veggie and gluten free sensitivity menu with awesome options! They’re very conscious of allergens and don’t compromise on flavor. The orange chicken serving was enough for 2-3 people and the Kimchi stew was a favorite at my table! Below is the GF wok fried shrimp bowl which was full of spice (not spicy spice necessarily) and flavor. Will Definitely return! They have brunch and gf desserts too!

Kimchi stew was great; the pork was tender and broth was flavorful, though I kind of wished there was a little more heat in the overall dish. Comfort food that made me feel like I was at home (almost as good as my mom's). At 8pm on a Friday, I waited about 20 minutes. When I got to the head of the line, staff took my order before the table was ready so that the food would arrive more quickly once I was seated. Bill is settled beforehand as well. The only obvious downside to me here is that the dining area felt rather loud. I recognize that having a small space + open kitchen + music makes this somewhat inevitable, but "must speak with raised voice" is pretty accurate for this location.
Honestly amazed that a bowl of anything could taste as good as the cumin lamb stir fry did.

This Asian fusion place has almost a fast casual vibe. Strong favours from South and East Asian dishes are hard to miss, and the beautiful presentation in steel bowls is delightful. My favorite is the cumin Lamb noodles. They have a separate menu for vegetarian and vegan options. The portion size is huge. The seating area is not too big, so it might get crowded sometimes.

I've tried these guys a few times and I'm always left thinking "I paid that much for this!!". Today I decided to give them one last shot. I ordered their chicken bowl to go. You would think I'd get this in a real bowl-style to-go container like you would get elsewhere (like a salad place, Chipotles, Bibibop etc) so you can eat it right out of the bowl. Instead they gave it to me in a carry-out tub that required me to scoop out onto a plate. Sorry, this isn't supposed to be carry-out Chinese here. Heck, even carry-out Chinese at least separates the rice. Very disappointed with these guys.
Great tater tots and green beans,  generally large portions, good flavors, reasonable prices. New location, nice space not too full.
Ate too much, but food is delicious

Great little spot. Highly recomend the orangish chicken. The wings are great too but if your order them wet be prepared for a saucy mess trying to eat them. There is very limited seating. Not a good place for large parties. Take out appeared very popular as multiple took food out while were there.
Delicious!

The place is top notch.  The people were so friendly and happy to have us.  They treated us like family and the owner sought us out and made sure we were amply taken care of.  The food is spicy and amazing flavor combinations.   We had the kimchi, cumin lamb noodles, dumplings, duck noodles, chicken/rice kids bowl, a bottle of fine and the coconut panicotta.
Phenomenal food, always impressed! Just know that its a fast casual experience so you go in with the right expectations when it comes to service
Great food, ok service.

Lives up to the hype.  Spicy wings were spicy, umami, not too sweet, and crispy, served so hot you can burn your month--watch out Bonchon.  Shrimp toast is made with super fresh shrimp in a balanced sauce/broth affair with lots of fresh garlic, chili, green onion, sesame, etc.  You mop it up with delicious light, fluffy, fresh white toast.  A little heat, but you'll barely notice after the wings--those really creep up on you in the best way possible.  Fair drink prices, yay for Mount Gay as house rum!  Staff is friendly and efficient at keeping folks moving through limited space with out making you feel rushed.
Ahhhmazing! Will be back ten times over! Everything was delicious!!

So it’s over one year that I have moved to DC and I have been searching for that a good  Chinese fried rice. A friend told me about Chiko, and I ordered online for the Chicken and Egg Fried Rice and the Double fried Chicken Wings. The rice was over cooked, poorly spiced, basic taste and also the same with the wings.
Great concept
The smell of the food from the outside lures you in. The food is absolutely delicious.
I'm not a foodie and I LOVED the food here. Literally everything was good. Go now!
Insanely good!!
Amazing food, great portions, and very accommodating for vegans!
The service is amazing. The staff is very nice.

Chiko is hands down the best value for your money in DC. The salmon rice bowl for lunch ($14) is filling and delicious. The chef’s counter will leave you with enough food for breakfast the next day ($50). Try the restaurant week lunch at the DuPont location - $22 for a full lunch spread!
Great service from Dylan and the CHIKO crew!  We had a wonderful meal...don't miss this gem!
My girlfriend after 5 hours she still have upset stomach. In my understanding they rush to cook, maybe not a good food handling.
Amazing food, amazing space, and amazing staff... definitely on my list of regular places to dine!
Amazing, such a great experience! Super flavorful and fun environment
A bit different more Korean Chinese fusion but that great.  Liked twice fried chicken wings and street something corns were good.

Chinese-Korean fusion excellently executed--this place was crowded when we visited, and for good cause. The food walks the line between familiar and unexpected. I had the brisket bowl, which was phenomenal. I'll definitely head back here again.

This place is so incredible!! The food was out of this world, incredibly well spiced, and very fast. While most DC restaurants charge hefty prices for small plates, this place charges hefty prices for LARGE ones! Salmon? Incredible! Orangish chicken? Amazing!
Good but slightly overpriced.

Great tasting food. I would definitely recommend for take out as dinning in requires you to pay tip before eating and service is not the greatest in space that’s a little too small. But overall good dishes.
Delish flavors and culinary excellence

I love the food, having been here & the 8th St location 3 times. But I will never return because of this chain’s business practice and its sub-par service  I. This chain employs practice that is questionable at best and unethical at worst  When you pay, you will notice three things. You will pay service/tip BEFORE you receive it. And you pay above market price (max = 25%, min = 18% even for lunch). And if you are a creature of habit, you will hit the 25% option as it is the left most. This is in contrast with typical POS, where left most is the minimum option.  Besides, your portion sizes vary location to location. My chicken wings had 4 in one spot, but 3 in the other. The way the staff dealt with this is why I have point 2.  II. The level of care and professionalism by the server I had was not worth the ask price (18 - 25%)  When confronted with the different portion sizes, my server did not check with the kitchen nor the manager on why. She ventured a guess that maybe there was different in wing sizes, price, etc; however, none of this holds water as I just visited the other location on Thursday of the same week. To make matters worst, she left and brought back a side dish to console us. To her credit, she brought the extra wing after noticing we didn’t touch the side dish.  In all, by all means try the food if you so wish. But I know it is not worth the annoyance I have with my experience.
Food was good and plenty. Reason for 3 stars is because staff member was rude when we took an extra chair from a party who weren't using it to accommodate 5 people at our table for 4.

I like this place a lot. The food is very, very good but I don't think the prices match the level of service at the restaurant. Not that the staff isn't friendly or helpful -- they're both, but the format of the restaurant is odd. It straddles a weird line between sit-down and fast casual. Food is brought to your table, but you're expected to refill your own water and the environment isn't particularly comfortable. All this being said, this is worth at least one visit for the delicious food.
Amazing tasting menu. Sample 90% of the menu. Would come back in a heartbeat - bring a second stomach because the portions are HUGE and DELICIOUS!!
Too heavy sauces and overcooked!

Couldn’t fit all the food we ordered (because we’ve already started eating and it was so good!). We ordered the Crispy Chicken (great crunch in the chicken and oh-so amazing peanut sauce!)and the Bulgogi (beef strips so soft they melt in your mouth).  We got in at the right time before the lunch crowd came in. Ordered tempura green beans to go and have a taste of CHIKO at home.  We’ll definitely come back for more.  *we’ve got our eyes set on the Cumin Lamb Stir Fry!  Thank you!

We recently had brunch here. Get the shrimp and grits and skip the brisket. The brisket was 95% rice and 5% meat with some pieces chewy. For $18, give some veggies to make it a more balance dish. A total letdown. Service was friendly.
Modern twist on chinese/korean. Good vibe Good to great food.

Busy as can be, but the place runs well. You wait in line, order, and then sit and your food comes to your numbered table when it is ready. Overall the food was pretty darn good with a few misses. It all comes hot and looks scrumptious. The crispy spring rolls had an amazing crunch and elongated look, but the inside was less than expected, if fact I'd go as far as to say they were bland. The green beans were fresh and well seasoned. The fried chicken was messy sweet and delicious. I would go back, but be a tad choosy.  Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz

Took my partner here for his birthday and did the $50 “eat the menu” option at the counter. Amazing experience in every way. Exceptional service, fun atmosphere, and incredible food! Every single item was delicious - and the portion was HUGE - it really is eating the entire menu. They offered plenty of boxes for leftovers! Unforgettable experience and unbelievably good food! Can’t recommend highly enough, and I’m usually pretty picky.
Tasting experience is an amazing meal!

I stopped here for lunch. Although it has an Asian flare I wouldn't classify it as Korean. I had the salad and some wings. The wings were good but if ur looking for the traditional Korean fried chicken don't get the dry version.
(Translated by Google) The liver is a little crazy, but there is a taste.  (Original) 간이 좀 쎄긴한데 맛은 있음 글구 직원들이 엄청최고진짜 친절보스
All the dishes we had were delicious:very rich in flavors.
Excellent food and value in a semi-fast food environment
I love the portion size. Plenty of food and it’s super delicious. It’s truly a modern Asian cuisine that can satisfy all palettes.
Come here ready to wait 40 minutes for your food.

We tried the chicken fried rice and the cumin lamb noodle stir fry. Going by the description in the menu and the prices, we really expected something special!  But the food was amateurish. The flavors in the rice were a muddle, and it was texturally boring. The green peas in the fried rice really didn't work for me. The spices in the cumin stir fry weren't tempered and really didn't blend well together. There also wasn't enough cumin in the cumin stir fry and the noodles were overcooked. Fusion food is hard to get right. I'd hoped Chiko would manage it, but I was wrong.

Not bad but not great as far as a restaurant serving a mixture of Asian foods is concerned. Kimchi stew was good with very tender pork belly. While reminiscent of traditional Uyghur cuisine and flavorful the lamb curry noodles had way overcooked noodles. Friend rice wasn't bad. Shrimp and toast was okay, not what we expected when we ordered but we didn't read the description well enough I guess. None of the food was spicy according to my palate and the hot sauce that the waiter warned us about peaked at a 3 out 10 on the spicy scale.

An amazing diiner tonight. Dish after dish was superb. And Dylan, our waiter, rocked. Handled a mix up on our reservation with aplomb and treated us to a great meal. Do not miss either shrimp dish, the kimchi or the Wagshal’s brisket.
Yum

What a fun place to eat, assuming you have no mobility issues and can get up the 11 steps to the door.  The staff were so upbeat and friendly, it was contagious.  Although warned it was spicy, which it was, the cumin lamb stir fry was delicious.  Faced with the dilemma of eating it all or leaving room for dessert, I ordered the pricey,  but worth it, coconut custard.  It got crowded and noisy around noon, so if you want a quiet meal, go for an early (it opens at 11:00 a.m.) or late lunch.  Forks are available upon request.

A must see in DC! Inspired by Chinese and Korean cuisines they serve dishes you won't find anywhere else. There is a meal that's even exclusive to this location of Chiko restaurants. Very intimate atmosphere and a high paced environment. Also, it's a lot of food, so you are likely to have left overs.

Sat at counter and had an amazing time. Server Brandon was awesome and the food was super dank. Small and bright space, no real need to dress up. Will come back for the toast&shrimp and orange chicken.
Cool spot, the food is great and nicely creative. Mildly pricey for what you get, but certainly worth at least on visit (if not several).
Ordered the kimchi stew, the broth and pork were really flavorful. Tho, it's a very small place, long waits during dinner time and not good for groups. Plus there's no table service.
New location!

The Chef's Table was an awesome experience. From the opening appetizers to the desert everything on the menu was flavorful and prepared perfectly. Almost everything on the menu was on the Chef's Table experience so if you want great take out or a night out with friends, check out CHIKO!
Service, music, food are great. You can’t ask for more. Brandon the manager is the man. Love this spot.

Went for dinner and everything was great. We had the orange ish chicken and the lamb noodle dish. The flavors were great in both with our favorite being the chicken. It has the right amount of crisp to it. The lamb was very tasty and spicy so would recommend if  you are looking for a spicy dish. You order when you get in and they bring the food to your table. I will definitely go again. Pictures of our dishes attached.
